equation_narrative.headline: Proline emerges late from polar-hydrophobic ambiguity via specialized MLP channels
equation_narrative.story: Position 37 sits in a context that initially appears polar-hydrophobic ambiguous, with serine leading the logit lens at 22.6% at embedding and hydrophobic residues (L, V, A) dominating through layer 23. The model reads 3 structural contacts but receives no co-evolutionary signal, assembling a representation consistent with small, flexible residues in a turn-like environment. The decision crystallizes late: proline-specific MLP neurons activate strongly at L27-28 (N27:2753, N28:2865 with 0.52-0.68 projection), and proline surges from 14.5% at L23 to 71% at L33, overcoming a brief challenge from alanine at L31 (44.8%).

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 assemble a representation with conflicting chemical character. The logit lens initially projects toward polar residues (S at 22.6% at L0), then shifts through hydrophobic candidates (V, L dominate L3-17, peaking at 35.5% for L at L10). Structural attention is minimal—only 3 contacts are read, suggesting this position is relatively isolated or surface-exposed. No co-evolutionary signal arrives (0 coevolving positions), indicating functional independence. By L18, the representation shifts back toward polar character (S rises to 20.1%), and proline begins its slow ascent from 2.5% at L17 to 14.5% at L23. The representation appears to encode a position requiring both flexibility and small size, consistent with a turn or loop environment.
perception_phase.context_character: The context by L23 is ambiguous: small, polar-hydrophobic flexible residues are favored. The structural environment appears surface-exposed or loop-like (minimal structural contacts, no burial signature). The logit lens shows nearly equal support for S (26.2%), A (13.7%), and emerging P (14.5%).
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: only 3 residues within contact distance, suggesting surface exposure or loop position
No co-evolutionary signal: 0 coevolving positions indicates functional independence
L18 attention features: F18:4071 (19.2 proj) and F18:1860 (18.7 proj) encode turn-like or flexible context
L9 hydrophobic phase: F9:5728 (55.8 proj) reflects transient hydrophobic character from local sequence reading

decision_phase.summary: The decision phase begins at L24-25 with proline-specific prediction channels activating. N24:3615 (0.55 proj) and N24:2304 (0.40 proj) cast strong votes for proline, pushing it from 14.5% to 18% by L25. The decisive surge occurs at L27-28: N27:2753 (0.52 proj) and N28:2865 (0.68 proj) drive proline from 18% to 36.8%. A brief challenge from alanine at L31 (44.8% vs P's 36.8%) is resolved by L32, where proline reaches 57.9% and ultimately 71% at L33. Late-layer SAE features (F30:5918, F30:160 with 23+ projection) and attention heads (F33:9048, 78.6 proj) consolidate the proline prediction.
decision_phase.transition: The L23-25 boundary marks the shift from context assembly to amino acid commitment. At L23, the representation still balances S (26.2%), A (13.7%), and P (14.5%) with no clear winner. By L25, proline-specific MLP neurons (N24:3615, N25:3342) activate, and proline rises to 18%. The first AA-specific prediction features appear at L24 (F24:5080 with 27.5 proj), signaling the transition from 'what context is here' to 'which amino acid fits this context.'

candidates.narrative: Proline emerges as the winner through late-phase MLP activation. It remains below 15% through L23, then surges via specialized neurons: N24:3615 (0.55 proj), N27:2753 (0.52 proj), and N28:2865 (0.68 proj) drive it from 14.5% at L23 to 36.8% at L28. After a brief dip when alanine peaks at L31 (44.8%), proline recovers decisively at L32 (57.9%) and reaches 71% at L33. Late SAE features F30:5918 (23.7 proj) and F33:9048 (78.6 proj) consolidate the prediction.
candidates.key_layers: Emerges L24-25, surges L27-28, dominant by L32

N27:2753 (0.52 proj) — proline vote with secondary E support

candidates.narrative: Alanine is the runner-up, briefly leading at L31 with 44.8% before losing to proline. It maintains steady support through the perception phase (13.7% at L23, 17.3% at L29) as the representation encodes small, hydrophobic-compatible character. The L31 peak is driven by attention (head writes at L30-31), but MLP neurons fail to sustain it—proline's specialized channels (N32:2302 with 0.82 proj) overpower alanine's more diffuse support, and it falls to 13.5% by L33.
candidates.key_layers: Steady through L29, peaks L31 (44.8%), collapses L32-33
key_evidence: N32:2302 (0.82 proj for P) — proline neuron that erases alanine's lead

candidates.narrative: Serine leads the logit lens at embedding (22.6%) and resurges at L18-24 (peaks 46.4% at L24), reflecting the representation's polar character during context assembly. This is NOT a model prediction—it indicates the representation is consistent with polar, small residues as the model reads local sequence and structural context. Serine's logit-lens prominence reflects the position's turn-like, flexible environment. Once proline-specific decision channels activate at L24+, serine's support collapses (26.2% at L23 → 6.7% at L33) as the model commits to the structurally constrained proline.
candidates.key_layers: Leads L0, resurges L18-24 (peak 46.4%), collapses L25+
key_evidence: L24 peak: 46.4% — representation encodes polar-flexible character
Collapse after L24 as proline channels activate

candidates.narrative: Leucine dominates the logit lens during the hydrophobic phase (L8-17), peaking at 35.5% at L10. This reflects the representation's transient hydrophobic character as the model reads local sequence context (flanking residues include hydrophobic positions). The logit lens projects toward leucine because the accumulated features at L10 are hydrophobic-leaning, NOT because the model predicts leucine. Once the representation shifts toward polar-flexible character at L18+ and proline channels activate at L24+, leucine's support evaporates (9.5% at L23 → 1.9% at L33).

key_evidence: Collapse to 1.9% as polar-flexible representation emerges

turning_points.description: The representation shifts from hydrophobic to polar-flexible character. Leucine's logit-lens dominance (35.5% at L10) collapses as serine resurges (20.1% at L18 → 26.2% at L23). Attention features F18:4071 (19.2 proj) and F18:1860 (18.7 proj) encode turn-like or loop context. Proline begins its slow rise from 2.5% to 14.5%, signaling the representation is converging toward a structurally constrained, flexible position. This is the model recognizing 'what kind of position this is' before committing to a specific amino acid.

The decision phase begins. Proline-specific MLP neurons activate: N24:3615 (0.55 proj) and N24:2304 (0.40 proj) at L24, followed by the decisive surge at L27-28 via N27:2753 (0.52 proj) and N28:2865 (0.68 proj). Proline rises from 14.5% at L23 to 36.8% at L28. MLP layer 28 shows total answer projection of 0.71, driven by 4.79 from the MLP stream (largest MLP contribution in the decision phase). Serine collapses from 26.2% to 16.2% as proline channels dominate.

Alanine briefly challenges proline, peaking at 44.8% at L31 via attention-driven writes. However, proline's MLP support proves decisive: N32:2302 (0.82 proj) and N32:4345 (0.63 proj) push proline from 36.8% to 57.9%, reclaiming the lead. Attention head L32:12 acts as a structural eraser (-1.99 proj), suppressing competing candidates. By L33, proline reaches 71% with final consolidation from F33:9048 (78.6 proj) and F33:2787 (78.4 proj).

deep_dives.caption: MLP layers 24-25 activate the first proline-specific prediction channels. N24:3615 (0.55 proj) and N24:2304 (0.40 proj) push proline from 14.5% to 18%, marking the transition from perception to decision.

deep_dives.caption: Layer 31-32 MLP neurons resolve the alanine challenge. N32:2302 (0.82 proj for P) and N32:4345 (0.63 proj for P) overpower alanine's attention-driven peak, restoring proline's dominance.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts proline by recognizing position 37's turn-like, structurally constrained environment. Despite early ambiguity—the representation cycles through hydrophobic (L8-17) and polar (L18-24) character—specialized proline MLP neurons activate decisively at L27-28, leveraging the assembled context of small size, flexibility, and minimal structural contacts. The strongest evidence is the coordinated MLP surge at L27-28 (N27:2753, N28:2865 with 0.5-0.7 projection) combined with late attention consolidation (F33:9048, 78.6 proj), which together drive proline from 14.5% at L23 to 71% at L33, overcoming both early hydrophobic signals and a late alanine challenge.
